  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm a rookie. How should I start preparing for getting selected in GSoC 17?",
  "response": "Participating in Google Summer of Code (GSoC) can be a rewarding experience for aspiring developers. Here are some steps to help you prepare for GSoC 2017:\n\n1. **Understand GSoC:**\n   - Read through the official [GSoC website](https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com) to understand the program, its requirements, and the timeline.\n   - Study the FAQ and the guides provided for students.\n\n2. **Choose Organizations:**\n   - Browse the list of participating organizations from previous years to get an idea of which open-source projects are typically included.\n   - Look for organizations that match your interest and skill set.\n\n3. **Get Involved Early:**\n   - Start contributing to the organizations you are interested in. Visit their websites, join their mailing lists, and participate in their community forums or IRC channels.\n   - Familiarize yourself with their repositories on platforms like GitHub or GitLab.\n   - Try to solve some of the issues labeled as \"beginner\" or \"good first issue.\"\n\n4. **Learn Relevant Skills:**\n   - Brush up on coding skills in languages and technologies relevant to your chosen organizations.\n   - Work on personal projects or contribute to other open-source projects to build a portfolio and improve your proficiency.\n\n5. **Read Documentation:**\n   - Read and understand the documentation of the projects you are interested in.\n   - Browse through past proposals to get an idea of what successful proposals look like. Many organizations provide templates or advice on writing proposals.\n\n6. **Engage with Mentors:**\n   - Engage with potential mentors early on. Ask questions, seek feedback on your contributions, and express your interest in participating in GSoC.\n   - Demonstrating your commitment and enthusiasm can help you make a good impression.\n\n7. **Prepare Your Proposal:**\n   - Start drafting your project proposal well before the submission deadline.\n   - Clearly define your project idea, timeline, milestones, and deliverables.\n   - Ensure that your proposal is specific, achievable, and aligns with the organization's goals.\n\n8. **Seek Feedback:**\n   - Share your proposal draft with mentors and ask for feedback.\n   - Incorporate the feedback to refine your proposal.\n\n9. **Stay Updated:**\n   - Keep an eye on announcements related to GSoC 2017 on the GSoC website and the organizations' communication channels.\n   - Adhere to all deadlines and requirements.\n\n10. **Network:**\n    - Connect with past GSoC participants to gain insights and tips.\n    - Attend relevant conferences, meetups, or webinars if possible.\n\nRemember, starting early and being proactive are key to increasing your chances of being selected for GSoC. Good luck!",
